        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Here is something that i though you guys might enjoy reading and another reason why I'm frustrated with VI. To give you a basic history of the events. I recently did the quest for jboots. Hasten was on his rag so he took my items and no boots. After a week of haveing my petiotion esclated I finally got a GM to reimburse my shadowed raiper, the ring , but no money. GM indicated that there was a problem with the gold turn in and i need to re-supply it myself. Had no problem with it since the only thing in my mind was the ring. Two days later i attempted to do the quest again with the same result. Wana be Yoda said something like "Trade we shall not!" and still no boots. So after another week of Guides they told me i should e-mail for quiker responce. So I did and what follows is the back and forth e-mails. (ohh forgot to mention. The first and the second time i did the quest there were other people complainging that yoda has gone mad and they got riped off.)

ME:
problemdate: 7/17/02

problemType: Item Missing

Hello. I did the Journeyman Boots quest today and Hesten did not give me
the quest item after turning in 3250 gp, shadowed raiper and a ring of
the Ancients. This is the second time I'm haveing a problem with this
quest. The first time a GM said that there might have been a problem
with the gold turn in and returned the ring and the raiper. Same thing
happened today. Also another character by the name of caimbree did the
quest less than a minute after me with the same resault. Any help in
this matter wiould be greatly appricated.
Thank you

VI:
Greetings.

Thank you for contacting EverQuest In-Game Customer Support.  

It appears that your issue has already been resolved. Please let us know
if this is not the case.

Sincerely,

-------------------------------------------
Patrick O'Hara
EverQuest CSR - Ashescura
Sony Online Entertainment
http://www.station.sony.com
